the normal lithium batteries

00:01:53.270 --> 00:01:55.620
that are sitting in
your phones will not

00:01:55.620 --> 00:01:58.620
work all the way up there,
because they'll just freeze.

00:01:58.620 --> 00:02:00.690
We actually have to
hook our phones up

00:02:00.690 --> 00:02:02.280
to external battery
packs that are

00:02:02.280 --> 00:02:05.380
using disposable lithium
primary batteries.

00:02:05.380 --> 00:02:07.160
I actually do all this
in my living room.

00:02:07.160 --> 00:02:09.639
I just have a little
bench, and you don't really

00:02:09.639 --> 00:02:11.950
need that much to do
a project like this.

00:02:11.950 --> 00:02:13.800
HEATHER BRUNDAGE: Our
most basic payload

00:02:13.800 --> 00:02:15.400
is just an Android phone.

00:02:15.400 --> 00:02:18.900
And with that phone, we're able
to get GPS location, as well

00:02:18.900 --> 00:02:20.090
as altitude.

00:02:20.090 --> 00:02:22.280
Android allowed
us to take control

00:02:22.280 --> 00:02:24.360
of the phone in a low-level
way that we needed.

00:02:24.360 --> 00:02:25.790
We're using these
phones in a way

00:02:25.790 --> 00:02:28.660
that they're not designed
for, and other phones

00:02:28.660 --> 00:02:29.900
don't let you do that.

00:02:29.900 --> 00:02:32.400
VIMAL BHALODIA: So the app that
we developed for our balloon

00:02:32.400 --> 00:02:34.380
launches is pretty
much the polar opposite

00:02:34.380 --> 00:02:36.760
of a normal
well-behaved mobile app.

00:02:36.760 --> 00:02:38.770
A normal well-behaved
mobile app tries

00:02:38.770 --> 00:02:40.960
to be very careful
about power consumption.

00:02:40.960 --> 00:02:43.360
It tries to play well with
all the other apps that

00:02:43.360 --> 00:02:43.860
are running.

00:02:43.860 --> 00:02:45.870
It doesn't want
to hog resources.

00:02:45.870 --> 00:02:47.640
We want it to be
running all the time.

00:02:47.640 --> 00:02:49.150
We never want it to sleep.

00:02:49.150 --> 00:02:52.650
We want it to always be the most
important app that is running.

00:02:52.650 --> 00:02:55.080
And make sure that, if
for whatever reason,

00:02:55.080 --> 00:02:57.130
the phone reboots
because of a low power

00:02:57.130 --> 00:02:59.339
situation or something, our
app comes up and running.

00:02:59.339 --> 00:03:00.755
HEATHER BRUNDAGE:
That's something

00:03:00.755 --> 00:03:03.580
that a lot of other phones don't
allow you to have access to,

00:03:03.580 --> 00:03:06.050
but Android allowed us
to have that control.

00:03:06.050 --> 00:03:08.091
VIMAL BHALODIA: And there's
our phone booting up.

00:03:08.091 --> 00:03:09.160
Good times.

